cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

The paper presents an approach for generating whole-body motions for a humanoid robot, which involves optimization and control techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), which deals with the design, construction, operation, and use of robots. The paper also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper uses simulation and experimental implementation of several whole-body actions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could also place it in the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
